## git shortcuts for command line

:log // see the commit log of the current branch

:gce // make an empty commit to start off your issue branch

:add // stage all changed, added, and deleted files

:amend // amend the previous commit on the current branch
 
:branches // list all your local branches and their last commit

:git-local // open the git config for the repo you are in

:d-local // delete current branch locally

:d-remote // delete current branch on origin


## git shortcuts for editor

:message // commit message template (use in editor)


## general shortcuts

:zsh // open your .zshrc 

:date // current date

